<item>
            <title>[SPARK-39783] Column backticks are misplaced in the AnalysisException [UNRESOLVED_COLUMN] error message when using field with &quot;.&quot;</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-39783</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;AnalysisException &lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;UNRESOLVED_COLUMN.WITH_SUGGESTION&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; shows the wrong suggestion when a field with the &quot;.&quot; separator is referenced without backticks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following code references a nested value &lt;tt&gt;`the`.`id`&lt;/tt&gt;, that does not exist. The proposed / existing column names are not correctly wrapped in backticks:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-scala&quot;&gt;
Seq((0)).toDF(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;the.id&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
  .select(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;the.id&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).show()

org.apache.spark.sql.AnalysisException: [UNRESOLVED_COLUMN.WITH_SUGGESTION] A column or function parameter &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;with&lt;/span&gt; name `the`.`id` cannot be resolved. Did you mean one of the following? [`the`.`id`];
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Instead of suggesting &lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;`the`.`id`&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt; in the &lt;b&gt;error message&lt;/b&gt;, you would expect suggesting &lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;`the.id`&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
